SMALL MODEL SHAREWARE VERSION - Feel free to distribute these files in
                                unmodified form.
    
    This disk comprising EnQue's InTUItion Library V1.01 10/10/91 contains:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------
	
	tuiv101.ver  - this file signifies the version of the InTUItion Library.
	lib.zip      - The small model libraries for Turbo/Borland C and Microsoft.
	help.zip     - the InTUItion documentation in hypertext ASCII format.
	hdr.zip      - the InTUItion "C" header files.
	source.zip   - the InTUItion "C" source files (not included) and executables.
  pkunzip.exe  - used to unzip the above zip files.
	install.exe  - the InTUItion Library installation program.
	readme       - this short file.

If you are upgrading from a previous version of InTUItion, the installation
program will overwrite existing files of the same name, thereby upgrading
them.  However, if older version header files reside in more than one
directory, be sure to remove them as the new header files must be used.

To install these zip files, simply type a:install (assuming this disk is
is drive a) and select the desired portions to install, the destination
drive and paths, and press the 'k' (OK) key.  You may also simply unzip
the files into the desired directories.

The small model libraries for Turbo/Borland C and Microsoft C are included
in lib form.

To playback the tutorials, simply type "tuicp -pfname" where fname is
one of menu.tut, help.tut, button.tut, or entry.tut and sit back and 
enjoy!

All documentation is in hypertext help format and can be accessed using the
included enqhelp.exe or printed using prt_help.exe.  The source code for
the install program is included as an additional example of using InTUItion.


